cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of human pose prediction. The use of deep reinforcement learning methods also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of behavioral cloning and generative adversarial imitation learning could suggest that it belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the focus on training speed could suggest that it belongs to the systems and control (cs.SD) sub-category.
